== Career == In {{ill|Jishō|ja|治承|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year (1180), when Minamoto no Yoshinaka raised an army, Mitsumori joined as a prominent commander. In {{ill|Juei|ja|寿永|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year (1183), he participated in the {{ill|Battle of Shinohara|ja|篠原の戦い|12=draft|12=draft}}. An episode from this battle is notable in the {{ill|The Tale of the Heike|ja|平家物語|12=draft|12=draft}}, where Mitsumori defeated {{ill|Saitō Sanemori|ja|斎藤実盛|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Sanemori, concealing his old age by dyeing his white hair black, fought valiantly in the colors of the general {{ill|Taira no Koremori|ja|平維盛|12=draft|12=draft}}. After a fierce duel, Mitsumori brought Sanemori's head back to Yoshinaka's camp. When the head was washed, the dye faded, revealing white hair. Recognizing the man as his savior during childhood, Yoshinaka wept openly.<ref>The Tale of the Heike.</ref>
In {{ill|Juei|ja|寿永|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year (1184), during the {{ill|Battle of Awazu|ja|粟津の戦い|12=draft|12=draft}}, Mitsumori fought against the armies of {{ill|Minamoto no Noriyori|ja|源範頼|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|12=draft|12=draft}}, dying alongside his lord Yoshinaka. He was one of the last loyal retainers to Yoshinaka.
== Descendants and Legacy == Tezuka Mitsumori is associated with several legends and remains: * His grave is located in {{ill|Tezuka area|ja|手塚 (上田市)|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ueda, Nagano|ja|上田市|12=draft|12=draft}}. * The Tezuka clan changed their surname to Tetsuka and established a memorial for Mitsumori in Osaka's {{ill|Tezukayama|ja|帝塚山|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Mitsumori's lineage is said to include: * Tezuka Mitsuharu, a descendant who served as a {{ill|rangaku|ja|蘭学|12=draft|12=draft}} scholar. * {{ill|Osamu Tezuka|ja|手塚治虫|12=draft|12=draft}}, a famous manga artist, is believed to be a 9th-generation descendant.<ref>Osamu Tezuka’s work "Phoenix" ("Civil War Chapter") references his lineage.</ref> == See Also == * {{ill|Suwa Taisha|ja|諏訪大社|1=Suwa-taisha|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kanemasa clan|ja|金刺氏|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|ja|源義仲|12=draft|12=draft}}
